Tanzania Sugar Costs Increase On Shortage, Daily News Newspaper Reports

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-08-30T03:35:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-30/tanzania-sugar-costs-increase-on-shortage-daily-news-newspaper-reports.html
The cost of sugar in Tanzania has
increased as factories suspend production of the sweetener,
Daily News reported, citing Castor Raphael, Chairman Tanzania
Sugar Board.  A kilogram of sugar now costs between 2,200 Tanzanian
shillings and 2,500 shillings, comapred with an average of 600
shillings two weeks ago, the Dar es Salaam-based newspaper
reported. Sugar consumption in  East Africa â€™s second biggest
economy is 400,000 tons annually, the newspaper said. The
government has issued permits to import the shortage, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
